content:
Sure, here's an example of an HTML page along with the CSS to display a list of 5 outdoor activities you can do in your hometown this summer. Replace `[Your Hometown]` with the name of your hometown.

### HTML Code:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Summer Activities in [Your Hometown]</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Summer Activities in [Your Hometown]</h1>
    </header>
    <main>
        <section class="activity">
            <img src="beach.jpg" alt="Beach" />
            <h2>Beach Day</h2>
            <p>Enjoy a relaxing day at the beach, soaking up the sun and splashing in the waves.</p>
        </section>
        <section class="activity">
            <img src="hiking.jpg" alt="Hiking" />
            <h2>Mountain Hiking</h2>
            <p>Explore scenic trails and enjoy breathtaking views from the top of the mountains.</p>
        </section>
        <section class="activity">
            <img src="cycling.jpg" alt="Cycling" />
            <h2>Cycling Tour</h2>
            <p>Take a cycling tour through the beautiful countryside and discover hidden gems.</p>
        </section>
        <section class="activity">
            <img src="picnic.jpg" alt="Picnic" />
            <h2>Park Picnic</h2>
            <p>Pack a picnic and enjoy a day outdoors with family and friends in a local park.</p>
        </section>
        <section class="activity">
            <img src="boating.jpg" alt="Boating" />
            <h2>Boating Adventure</h2>
            <p>Set sail on a boating adventure and explore the waterways of [Your Hometown].</p>
        </section>
    </main>
</body>
</html>
```

### CSS Code (styles.css):

```css
body {
    font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    background-image: url('background.jpg');
    background-size: cover;
    color: #333;
}

header {
    background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
    padding: 20px;
    text-align: center;
}

h1 {
    font-size: 2.5em;
    margin: 0;
}

main {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: center;
    padding: 20px;
}

.activity {
    background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
    border-radius: 10px;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    margin: 15px;
    width: 300px;
    text-align: center;
    overflow: hidden;
}

.activity img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
}

.activity h2 {
    margin: 10px 0;
    font-size: 1.5em;
}

.activity p {
    font-size: 1em;
    padding: 0 10px 20px;
}

@media (max-width: 600px) {
    main {
        flex-direction: column;
        align-items: center;
    }

    .activity {
        width: 90%;
    }
}
```

### Notes:

- The images (`beach.jpg`, `hiking.jpg`, `cycling.jpg`, `picnic.jpg`, `boating.jpg`, `background.jpg`) should be replaced with actual image files or URLs pointing to the images you would like to use.
- You can replace `'Arial'` with a custom font by importing it via Google Fonts or any other font provider. Just add the font import link in the `<head>` of your HTML file.
- Remember to update the `[Your Hometown]` placeholder with the name of your hometown.
